Welcome to the W3C {{ group.name }}!

Here's some quick links:


Meetings and communications channels:
=====================================

You can find information about the {{ group.name }} linked from:
https://www.w3.org/groups/{{ shorttype }}/{{ group.shortname }}/

For meetings, check the group calendar at:
https://www.w3.org/groups/{{ shorttype }}/{{ group.shortname }}/calendar/

Currently, we hold CG meetings focused on specifications and roadmap discussions, as well as practitioners meetings focused on app development and concrete Solid applications

We communicate over Matrix on the following channels:

 - Practitioners: https://matrix.to/#/#solid-practitioners:matrix.org

 - Solid-CG: https://matrix.to/#/#solid_specification:gitter.im




Other helpful resources:
=========================


Our GitHub repository, where we keep technical reports and meeting minutes:
https://github.com/solid/specification

We have a catalog which gathers all the effort around Solid; if you have a project (even if still in a WIP state), please add a new record there:
https://solidproject.solidcommunity.net/catalog/#

For more general contributing, this is our guideline:  https://github.com/w3c-cg/solid/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md

All participants in the {{ group.name }} are expected to behave in accordance with the W3C Code of Conduct
https://www.w3.org/policies/code-of-conduct/ as well as the group charter https://www.w3.org/community/solid/charter/



If you have any questions or concerns, you can ask in the matrix channels above or contact the {{ group.name }} chair directly by email.

We are excited to have you!

Solid Community Group 
